Package org.apache.giraph.examples

Package of Giraph examples.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AggregatorsTestVertex
    Vertex which uses aggrergators.
    AggregatorsTestVertex.AggregatorsTestMasterCompute
    Master compute which uses aggregators.
    BloomFilter<E>
    Implementation of a Bloom-filter, as described here: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bloom_filter For updates and bugfixes, see http://github.com/magnuss/java-bloomfilter Inspired by the SimpleBloomFilter-class written by Ian Clarke.
    ConnectedComponentsVertex
    Implementation of the HCC algorithm that identifies connected components and assigns each vertex its "component identifier" (the smallest vertex id in the component) The idea behind the algorithm is very simple: propagate the smallest vertex id along the edges to all vertices of a connected component.
    FacilityLocation
    Demonstrates the basic Pregel PageRank implementation.
    FacilityLocation.FacilityLocationInputFormat
    Simple VertexInputFormat that supports FacilityLocation
    FacilityLocation.FacilityLocationMasterCompute
    Master compute associated with FacilityLocation.
    FacilityLocation.FacilityLocationOutputFormat
    Simple VertexOutputFormat that supports FacilityLocation
    FacilityLocation.FacilityLocationReader
    Simple VertexReader that supports FacilityLocation
    FacilityLocation.FacilityLocationWorkerContext
    Worker context used with FacilityLocation.
    FacilityLocationVertexValue  
    GeneratedVertexReader<I extends WritableComparable,V extends Writable,E extends Writable>
    Used by GeneratedVertexInputFormat to read some generated data
    IdentityVertex<I extends WritableComparable,V extends Writable,E extends Writable,M extends Writable>
    User applications can subclass IdentityVertex, which simply prints the results that have been read for testing IO related jobs under any inputformat
    IntPairWritable  
    LongDoubleDoubleTextInputFormat
    Simple text-based VertexInputFormat for unweighted graphs with long ids.
    LongDoubleNullTextInputFormat
    Input format for unweighted graphs with long ids and double vertex values
    NormalizingLongDoubleDoubleTextInputFormat
    Simple text-based VertexInputFormat for unweighted graphs with long ids.
    PageRankVertex
    The PageRank algorithm, with uniform transition probabilities on the edges http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PageRank
    PartitionContextTestVertex
    Vertex to test the functionality of PartitionContext
    PartitionContextTestVertex.TestPartitionContextPartitionContext
    PartitionContext for TestPartitionContext
    PartitionContextTestVertex.TestPartitionContextWorkerContext
    WorkerContext for TestPartitionContext
    RandomWalkVertex<E extends Writable>
    Base class for executing a random walk on a graph
    RandomWalkVertexMasterCompute
    Master compute associated with RandomWalkVertex.
    RandomWalkWithRestartVertex
    Executes "RandomWalkWithRestart", a random walk on the graph which is biased towards a source vertex.
    RandomWalkWorkerContext
    Worker context for random walks.
    SimpleAggregatorWriter
    This is a simple example for an aggregator writer.
    SimpleCheckpointVertex
    An example that simply uses its id, value, and edges to compute new data every iteration to verify that checkpoint restarting works.
    SimpleCheckpointVertex.SimpleCheckpointComputation
    Actual computation.
    SimpleCheckpointVertex.SimpleCheckpointVertexMasterCompute
    Master compute associated with SimpleCheckpointVertex.
    SimpleCheckpointVertex.SimpleCheckpointVertexWorkerContext
    Worker context associated with SimpleCheckpointVertex.
    SimpleCombinerVertex
    Test whether messages can go through a combiner.
    SimpleFailVertex
    Vertex to allow unit testing of failure detection
    SimpleInDegreeCountVertex
    Simple function to return the out degree for each vertex.
    SimpleLongDoubleDoubleDoubleIdentityVertex
    A simple use of the Identity Vertex for taking care of Long, Double, Double, Double type Inputformat Good for use with io.LongDoubleDoubleAdjacencyListVertexInputFormat
    SimpleMasterComputeVertex
    Demonstrates a computation with a centralized part implemented via a MasterCompute.
    SimpleMasterComputeVertex.SimpleMasterCompute
    MasterCompute used with SimpleMasterComputeVertex.
    SimpleMasterComputeVertex.SimpleMasterComputeWorkerContext
    Worker context used with SimpleMasterComputeVertex.
    SimpleMsgVertex
    Test whether messages can be sent and received by vertices.
    SimpleMutateGraphVertex
    Vertex to allow unit testing of graph mutations.
    SimpleMutateGraphVertex.SimpleMutateGraphVertexWorkerContext
    Worker context used with SimpleMutateGraphVertex.
    SimpleOutDegreeCountVertex
    Simple function to return the out degree for each vertex.
    SimplePageRankVertex
    Demonstrates the basic Pregel PageRank implementation.
    SimplePageRankVertex.SimplePageRankVertexInputFormat
    Simple VertexInputFormat that supports SimplePageRankVertex
    SimplePageRankVertex.SimplePageRankVertexMasterCompute
    Master compute associated with SimplePageRankVertex.
    SimplePageRankVertex.SimplePageRankVertexOutputFormat
    Simple VertexOutputFormat that supports SimplePageRankVertex
    SimplePageRankVertex.SimplePageRankVertexReader
    Simple VertexReader that supports SimplePageRankVertex
    SimplePageRankVertex.SimplePageRankVertexWorkerContext
    Worker context used with SimplePageRankVertex.
    SimpleShortestPathsVertex
    Demonstrates the basic Pregel shortest paths implementation.
    SimpleSuperstepVertex
    Just a simple Vertex compute implementation that executes 3 supersteps, then finishes.
    SimpleSuperstepVertex.SimpleSuperstepVertexInputFormat
    Simple VertexInputFormat that supports SimpleSuperstepVertex
    SimpleSuperstepVertex.SimpleSuperstepVertexOutputFormat
    Simple VertexOutputFormat that supports SimpleSuperstepVertex
    SimpleSuperstepVertex.SimpleSuperstepVertexReader
    Simple VertexReader that supports SimpleSuperstepVertex
    SimpleTextVertexOutputFormat
    Simple text based vertex output format example.
    SimpleTriangleClosingVertex
    Demonstrates triangle closing in simple, unweighted graphs for Giraph.
    SimpleTriangleClosingVertex.IntArrayListWritable
    Utility class for delivering the array of vertices THIS vertex should connect with to close triangles with neighbors
    SimpleTriangleClosingVertex.Pair
    Quick, immutable K,V storage for sorting in tree set
    SimpleVertexWithWorkerContext
    Fully runnable example of how to emit worker data to HDFS during a graph computation.
    SimpleVertexWithWorkerContext.EmitterWorkerContext
    Example worker context to emit data as part of a superstep.
    SimpleVertexWithWorkerContext.SimpleVertex
    Actual vetex implementation
    VerifyMessage
    An example that simply uses its id, value, and edges to compute new data every iteration to verify that messages are sent and received at the appropriate location and superstep.
    VerifyMessage.VerifiableMessage
    Message that will be sent in VerifyMessage.VerifyMessageVertex.
    VerifyMessage.VerifyMessageMasterCompute
    Master compute associated with VerifyMessage.VerifyMessageVertex.
    VerifyMessage.VerifyMessageVertex
    Send and verify messages.
    VerifyMessage.VerifyMessageVertex.VerifyMessageVertexWorkerContext
    Worker context used with VerifyMessage.VerifyMessageVertex.
    VertexWithDoubleValueDoubleEdgeTextOutputFormat
    Simple vertex output format for weighted graphs.
    VertexWithDoubleValueNullEdgeTextOutputFormat
    Output format for vertices with a long as id, a double as value and null edges
